  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They told us we, we-- that's they are bringing-- look, when you don't know the language-- they told her we are going to Taganrog.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it is a sea there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That is the Azov Sea, which joined to the Black Sea.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we are going to work on a [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[POLISH]-- in Poland-- in Polish, [POLISH] is a-- is a basket.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we-- so we laughed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We said most probably that the sea [INAUDIBLE] the thing we will [INAUDIBLE] [LAUGHS] And so we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we arrived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was in the-- January--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "January, 1940.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What it was, the day when I left Chelm-- 11 days later on the 1st of-- on the 1st of December was the first pogrom.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was-- they collected the, the-- from the welfare-- the president from the welfare went from home to home.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] only men from 16 to 60-- had together on, on a plaza there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And apparently, when-- it was about 700 of them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they been already-- so the Germans were on bicycles, on, on horses, on, on motorbikes and dogs and had them all around.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they told them they are going to, to march to the Russian border to the Bug.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So at that time, a lot of-- a lot of got killed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father, I-- we met, still, in Lubon-- we met one, which knew my father, which survived.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He swam through there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Could you imagine in Poland in December that-- to swim in the river?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[SIGHS] It was-- so he told us that my father was in it, too.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
